The paper proposes a new method for pooling in graph neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning research. The paper also extensively evaluates the proposed method on multiple datasets and compares it to existing state-of-the-art methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
